\subsection{Initialising the runner}

The default shell runner opens an interactive PTY-backed shell, and the
default editor runner launches the configured editor on the user's TTY.
Both dependencies stay injectable so the execution logic remains easy to
test.

<<tutorial runner methods>>=
def __init__(
    self,
    store: StateStore,
    catalog: TutorialCatalog,
    *,
    shell_runner: Callable[..., ShellResult] = run_interactive_shell,
    editor_runner: Callable[..., EditorResult] = run_editor,
    question_runner: Callable[..., ShellResult] | None = None,
    allow_shell_checks: bool = False,
):
    """Initialise a runner with persistent state and a shell backend."""

    self.store = store
    self.catalog = catalog
    self.shell_runner = shell_runner
    self.editor_runner = editor_runner
    self.question_runner = question_runner or missing_question_runner
    self.allow_shell_checks = allow_shell_checks
@

