\subsection{Reviewing saved transcripts}

The review command wants the latest attempt for each step by default.
That means repeated failed attempts do not overwhelm the output, while the
most recent state of each step remains visible.

Review should also survive tutorial-file churn.  If the current catalog no
longer contains the tutorial ID, we fall back to the metadata that was
saved in the run record.

<<tutorial runner methods>>=
def review(
    self,
    tutorial_id: str,
    *,
    step_number: int | None = None,
    run_id: str | None = None,
) -> tuple[Tutorial, TutorialRun, tuple[StepTranscript, ...]]:
    """Return saved transcripts for review."""

    run = self.get_run(tutorial_id, run_id=run_id)
    tutorial = self.review_tutorial(tutorial_id, run)
    transcripts = latest_step_transcripts(run)
    if step_number is not None:
        step_index = step_number - 1
        transcripts = tuple(
            transcript
            for transcript in transcripts
            if transcript.step_index == step_index
        )
        if not transcripts:
            raise IndexError(
                f"No transcript recorded for step {step_number}."
            )
    return tutorial, run, transcripts
